casebody.data:
WARE v. SAMUELS. No. 60, Docket 20322. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Nov. 4, 1946. Joseph Goldberg, of New York City, for bankrupt-appellant. N. William Welling, of New York City, for trustee-appellee and objecting creditor-appellee.

Before AUGUSTUS N. HAND, CHASE and CLARK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed on the ground that the appeal only involves issues of fact, the disposition of which is not shown to have been erroneous.
